      id: 4,
      title: "Maturing vs Receding Hairline: Don't Let Hair Loss Control You",
      content:
        '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">A man’s head reflects his age. Noticing hair loss or a receding hairline can make you feel insecure and induce the desire to hide them. Many people do not know about maturing and receding hairlines. It is important to know the difference between the two, so you be cautious to prevent extreme hair loss. While one is due to normal ageing, another is caused by hair loss.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">To know more, keep reading the blog.</span></p><h1><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Why is understanding the maturing hairline important to know?</span></h1><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">In the shift from adolescence into adulthood, you see the visible changes in hair patterns. Just like skin ageing, the hairline moves backwards as you get old. This is where hair follicles thin and recede, but it\'s completely natural.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Your hairline typically moves back by about ½ to 1 inch, providing an M-shaped look. Generally, maturing hairline takes place between the ages of 17-30 years. The change will be very gradual and you will not experience excessive hair shedding or thinning.&nbsp;The Best Sign To Identify a Maturing Hairline is minimal hair loss. If there is no further significant thinning, the hair is likely maturing, not receding.</span></p><h1><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Understanding the concept of receding hairline</span></h1><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">You may have heard the word “male pattern baldness” specifically called “androgenic alopecia”, which causes receding hairline. It shows up when hair follicles shrink due to hormonal fluctuations and genetic factors. This eventually results in permanent hair loss.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">It often occurs after the age of 50, but some may experience it earlier. Receding hairline usually takes place faster than maturing and can be significant through noticeable scalp exposure in the crown and temples.</span></p><h2><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Reasons for Receding Hairline</span></h2><ul class="list-disc list-outside leading-3 -mt-2"><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Hormones: a hormone called “DHT (dihydrotestosterone)” is responsible for the condition called “male pattern baldness”. If any of your ancestors had receding hairline, you might experience it earlier than usual.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Ageing: over time, as we age, our hair health deteriorates, leading hair follicles to shrink and produce finer hair strands.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Lifestyle factors: inadequate consumption of proper diet, sedentary lifestyle, and lack of exercise results in balding.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Stress: Constant stress can weaken hair health and trigger hair shedding frequently.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Medical conditions: certain medical conditions such as thyroid and PCOS or PCOD in women often result in unusual hair loss.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Genetics: pattern hair loss is commonly viewed as receding hair loss in genetics.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Measure your hairline stage</span></h2><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Your hair loss progression can be assessed by using a tool called the Norwood scale, where your hair loss ranges to seven distinct stages.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br></p><ul class="list-disc list-outside leading-3 -mt-2"><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Stage 1-2: minimal or no hair loss, slight change around the temples, known as mature hairline.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Stage 3: more receding in temples and balding can be initially noticeable, with significant deep M-shape recession.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Stage 4-7: visible hair loss in the temple and crown region, gradually leading to excessive hair loss, resulting in a large area of baldness.</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p></p></li></ul><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">If you are unsure of where you are, we can help you identify your stage. Not sure if your hairline is receding? Take our expert-recommended hair test to find out!</span></p><h2><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Natural preventive measures for hair loss</span></h2><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">It is not always medication to stop hair loss. A few simple and regular preventive measures will postpone your hair loss timeline.&nbsp;</span></p><ul class="list-disc list-outside leading-3 -mt-2"><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Healthy lifestyle changes&nbsp;</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Avoiding stress</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Using mild and sulphate-free shampoos</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Good hair and scalp care</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Using natural topical.</span></p></li></ul><h2><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Effective treatments for hair loss</span></h2><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Some medical treatments completely transform your bald head into naturally voluminous-looking hair. Consider these options.</span></p><ul class="list-disc list-outside leading-3 -mt-2"><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Minoxidil and finasteride</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Botox</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Platelet-rich-plasma therapy</span></p></li><li class="leading-normal -mb-2"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Stem cell therapy</span></p></li></ul><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0)">Knowing the proper reason for certain changes in hair patterns can be a matter of weight lifting from your head. Taking the right precautions and treatments can help slow down hair loss and maintain a healthy hairline. Certain treatment options have proven effective and efficacy improves when some natural methods are also taken along.</span></p>',
